      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the political side of it, but in the field, people talk about it like it's almost in their nature to fight over these things. like, how much of this is actually just political stuff vs how much is just the way these specific tribes have always lived? doesn't the cultural makeup itself make them more prone to these types of clashes compared to, say, more settled or urbanized groups?",
